						<summary>

						<p>Fragment of a slab lying in the Chennakēśavasvāmi temple.</p>						

						<p>[KAPILĒŚVARA] DĒVAMAHĀRĀJA.</p>						

						<p>15th Century A.D.</p>						

						<p>It may be assigned to 15th century on the basis of palaeography and internal evidence.</p>						

						<p>Fragmentary and damaged. Refers to consecration of [Ahobale] Īśvara, installation of <hi rend="italic">Jayastaṁbha</hi> by Narasiṁha (pā)truḍu the <hi rend="italic">vūligam</hi> of mahārāja.</p>						

						</summary>
